description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated Band 5 nurse to join the existing Locala Cardiology team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking the skills of an experienced nurse, previous knowledge or experience of cardiac conditions, especially heart failure would be advantageous but not essential as training would be provided by the team of specialist nurses &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to demonstrate knowledge of national and local issues and be committed to partnership working with other providers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of a team and working in conjunction with GP’s, mainstream nursing, social and secondary care services, you will provide a patient focused, co-ordinated case management approach across primary care. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The post holder will participate in and influence efforts across health and social services to shape the service, to support patient choice, improve quality of life, and promote self-management whilst adopting the community care team approach.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous applications need not apply.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Sharon Stockdale Cardiology Team Leader – 03033309605 or &lt;span&gt;Sharon.stockdale@locala.org.uk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
